OL,3,CNatalie McNally considered breaking up
OL,4,Cwith murder accused, court hears
OL,6,FShe said there had been a crowd in the
OL,7,Fhome on January 26 organising a vigil
OL,8,Fin memory of Ms McNally, which was to
OL,9,Ftake place two days later in Lurgan.
OL,11,FThe witness said McCullagh had been at
OL,12,Fthe home and she had offered to cook
OL,13,Fhim dinner and made him welcome.
OL,15,FShe told the court he had stayed for a
OL,16,Fcouple of hours before leaving.
OL,18,FShe said he then returned to the house
OL,19,Fwithin 20 minutes.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/10
